equipment.hackText:
You access the relay's routing table. The signal isn't broadcasting blindly -- it's {purple:targeting neural interfaces}. Cycling through known signatures, trying to wake their hosts from cryo. Yours was the only one that responded.

{bright:> INTERFACES CONTACTED: 847}
{bright:> INTERFACES RESPONDED: 1}
{bright:> RESPONDER: [YOUR SIGNATURE]}

signal.text:
At this height, the signal resolves into something almost coherent. Your {purple:implant} translates fragments:

{purple:...REMEMBER... COME HOME... THE WORK IS NOT FINISHED...}

ATLAS is waiting for you. It knows who you are -- even if you don't.

descent-entrance.description:
A heavy blast door at the base of the antenna, partially concealed by earth and debris. Someone has cleared the entrance recently. The door is {green:open}.

Beyond it, a service elevator shaft. The elevator is gone, but maintenance ladders line the walls, descending into total darkness. Cold air rises from below, carrying the faint smell of machine oil.

{bright:There's no coming back from this easily. Make sure you're prepared.}
